All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
addPartController
The Add Part controller class handles the user input as well as saving the data to be reflected on the Main Menu.
addProductController
The Add Product controller gets the user input and saves it to be reflected on the Main Menu.
InHouse
This InHouse class inherits from the part class with all fields and methods plus the machineID field
Inventory
The Inventory class provides the methods for the Parts and Products controllers to use
MainMenu
This is the Main Class, data for the Parts and Products tables are loaded when the program runs.
MainMenuController
The Main Menu controller class is where the TableViews are set up.
modifyPartController
The Modify Part controller class handles the data from the Main Screen, enables the user to modify it and saves it.
modifyProductController
The Modify Product controller class handles the data from the Main Screen, enables the user to modify it and saves it.
Outsource
This Outsource class inherits from the part class with all fields and methods plus the companyName field
Part
The Part class is the superclass for the InHouse and Outsource classes
Product
The Product class provides the fields and methods for working with the Product controllers as well as associated parts.
